1. Your code is not in a package. Put it in a package. JUnit&#39;s test 
runners do not properly work if your test is in the default package.

&gt;       public static void main(String[] args) {
&gt; 
&gt;             int input = Integer.parseInt(args[0]);
&gt;             double result = factorial(input);
&gt;             System.out.println(result);
&gt;             junit.textui.TestRunner.run(suite());
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;       }

2. Delete main(). The test runners do not invoke your main.

 From the command line:

java -cp junit.jar;yourCode.jar junit.textui.TestRunner
&gt; 
&gt; public static Test suite() {
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;         TestSuite suite = new
&gt; TestSuite(Factorial.class);
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;         return suite;
&gt;     }

3. Delete suite(). This is exactly what JUnit&#39;s test runners do by 
default, so this is superfluous.

&gt; public static double factorial(int x){
&gt;       if (x&lt;0)
&gt;             return 0.0;
&gt;             double fact = 1.0;
&gt;       while (x&gt;0)      {
&gt;             fact=fact*x;
&gt;             x=x-1;
&gt;       }
&gt;       return fact;
&gt;       }
&gt; }

4. You haven&#39;t written any tests here. Where are your methods that start 
with &quot;test&quot;?

